name: Summertime Heavy Aircraft at Calgary International Airport! 20+ Minutes of Plane Spotting
description:
While searching for footage for my earlier videos on the potential deals regarding WestJet and Air Transat, I came across a day's worth of footage from 2017 that I had never posted... Until now!

The summertime traffic hasn't changed a whole lot since 2017, with the obvious exception of WestJet's brand new Dreamliners, and Air Canada 787s in place of the 777s.

Nonetheless, I hope you enjoy these 12 heavy aircraft (Yes, the 757 is a grey area) arriving and/or departing a sunny Calgary International Airport.
